cost about $7 million to build out. The site is designed for fleet clients that are operating medium-duty and light-duty vehicles in the Los Angeles area and features enough space for 42 vehicles; it is not designed for 18-wheelers. 

The 27,000-square-foot site is located about a half-mile from the Interstate 710 Freeway, a major freight corridor coming out of the ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach. It contains 16 fast-charging stalls that can fully charge a vehicle in about 30 minutes and 26 Level 2 charging stalls capable of charging vehicles in a couple hours. 

Axis IOS recently signed up its first tenant for the charging facility, Moxion Power, a Richmond-based company that makes zero-emission generators and off-road equipment for industrial and commercial purposes.

sites.notes:
The sales price was confirmed by the listing broker and one of the buyer's brokers. The sale is comprised of an industrial warehouse building totaling 82,775 SF that sits on 11.24 acres of land located at 2420 Yates Ave. in Commerce, CA. The sales price was reported at $41,350,000 or $84,47/SF of land, since it sold for land value only. The subject property was not listed on the market for sale; therefore, the sale was an off-market transaction. The seller, AT&T , is leasing back the property, but we were unable to verify the terms of their lease. The property contains no deferred maintenance. The sale was an all cash transaction.

The property is located close to a densley populated area. It is rare for low coverage 11-acre sites to become available in this market.

The motivation for the seller was to balance out their books.

The motivation for the buyer was most likely to eventually redevelop the property. With the vacancy rate at 2% in the central submarket, demand is strong for high-quality industrial real estate. Located minutes from downtown Los Angeles, the site at Yates Ave. provides immediate access to Interstate 5, the 710 Freeway, and the highly dense urban core. In addition, it offers long-term opportunities for flexible design and multiple uses.
